  "doc_id": "21316",
  "text": "The approach proposed by Geradts et al. [CITATION_1] aims at identifying the specific camera that generated one image by analyzing pixel defects. The authors considered hot pixels (individual pixels on the sensors with higher than normal charge leakage), cold pixels (pixels with lower than normal charge) and pixel traps (clusters of hot or cold pixels). The authors did not report quantitative results about the approach's effectiveness. The major problem of this technique is the fact that some cameras do not contain any defects and other cameras eliminate defective pixels by post-processing their images on-board.",
  "correct_citation": {
